# 📖 Introduction

Every time you open a website, your browser performs several operations behind the scenes within milliseconds.

Although it feels as simple as typing a URL and pressing Enter, the browser must first locate the correct server, establish a secure connection, request the webpage, receive the response, and finally render the website for you.

Understanding this process is the foundation of Web Security because every attack—whether SQL Injection, Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), or CSRF—takes place somewhere within this communication.

